
@{
    ViewBag.Title = "How it works";
}

    <h1 class="display-4 pt-3 text-center">The FODfinder <a class="font-weight-bold">Algorithm</a></h1>
<hr />
<div class="row justify-content-center">
    <div class="col-sm-8">
        <h2 class="pt-3">Why is a food rated as <a class="font-weight-bold">High</a> FODMAP?</h2>
        <div class="container">
            <h4><small class="text-muted">A food rated as "High FODMAP" could be comprised of 5% or more high FODMAP ingredients. While everyone is unique, any food listed as high FODMAP is likely to cause discomfort and other accompanying symptoms if eaten by someone with IBS.</small></h4>
        </div>

        <h2 class="pt-3">Why is a food rated as <a class="font-weight-bold">Medium</a> FODMAP?</h2>
        <div class="container">
            <h4><small class="text-muted">A food rated as "Medium FODMAP" could be comprised of between 0% and 5% high FODMAP ingredients. A food with a "Medium FODMAP" rating should most likely still be avoided by IBS sufferers or anyone attempting a low FODMAP diet.</small></h4>
        </div>

        <h2 class="pt-3">Why is a food rated as <a class="font-weight-bold">Low</a> FODMAP?</h2>
        <div class="container">
            <h4><small class="text-muted">Any food rated as "Low FODMAP" contains no known high FODMAP ingredients and should be safe to eat for anyone on a low FODMAP diet.</small></h4>
        </div>
        <div class="d-flex justify-content-center pt-4">
            <p>Note: The algorithm has been updated to include user labeled high-risk and low-risk ingredients!</p>
        </div>
    </div>
</div>